<TITLE> JU English students protest Shikha's death </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka Apr 3 (bdnews24.com)  Students of Jahangirnagar University's English department protested against the national authority's lack of attention towards road safety on the university campus on Saturday. The protest was triggered by the death of a student Saima Siddiqua Shikha, of the 32nd batch, awaiting her master's result. Shikha's classmates reminisced about her in the programme organised by the English department and students of her batch. The student's brought out a silent procession in the morning, blaming the negligence of the national authorities. The processionists also formed a human chain with placards and stayed at the Dairy Gate of the university for an hour. A condolence meeting was organised in a classroom of the department at noon. Saima Siddiqua Shikha died on the spot in a road accident that befell her on the way to her village home with her sister and mother on Mar 2
